Write a program to read two integers a and b. If b is not equal to '0', compute and print the value of "a/b" else, if b is equal to '0', raise an exception and print "ERROR..!!".

Sample Inputs	
7
-28	 

Sample Outputs
-0.25


 //Please accept the inputs from the console and print the output
 #include <stdio.h>
 #include<math.h>
 
 int main()
 {
 float a,b;
 scanf("%f%f", &a,&b);
 if(b==0){
     printf("ERROR..!!");
     return 0;
 }
 if(a<0){
     
     printf("%.1f", a/b);
     return 0;
 }
 printf("%.1f",a/b);
 return 0;
 }
 
